   MAR 31-APR 02, 2025},
Organization = {Institute of Electrical and Electronics Engineers Inc},
Abstract = {This essay explains why an automated vehicle (AV) manufacturer should
   consider law during the design process for an AV intended as
   ``fit-for-purpose{''} to transport intoxicated persons. It suggests that
   management, marketing, engineering and legal functions collaborate to
   develop product requirements and specifications that shield
   owner/occupants from criminal liability for DUI manslaughter, negligent
   homicide and similar charges, as well as guard against civil liability.
   This collaboration should occur for AV deployments in any state of the
   United States and in European countries.},
