   IEEE Student Branch},
Abstract = {When it comes to any type of crime it is just not a good picture to
   paint. Crime is a worldwide problem that directly or indirectly touches
   every one of us in multiple manners: as sufferers, in paying greater
   costs for merchandises and amenities, besides living with the concerns
   of fright and corruption. Moreover, location has a significant impact on
   crime. We propose a system to provide optimal travel route in Gurgaon,
   India (chosen as sample) along different modes of transport keeping in
   mind the distance and safety. We shall be using different learning
   algorithms to train the system based on available crime statistics
   (using research and surveys from government/ nongovernment
   organizations).},
