Abstract = {Rio de Janeiro is recognized as a violent city, but the pacifying police
   program was established with the goal to modify this situation. This
   paper shows that after six years and many pacified communities, the
   program has had an impact on the decrease of violent deaths with effects
   both before and after the deployment of the pacifying police units
   (UPPs). We also evidence a spatial dynamic where the neighboring areas
   to the UPPs present a more pronounced decrease. Those results raise new
   issues in the analysis of public safety.},
